 <purpose>
   The constructive solid geometry 3d application module supports the
   requirement to represent solid geometry models created using component
   primitives and a sequence of Boolean operations.  
 </purpose>

 <inscope>
   <li>the creation of constructive solid geometry models based on
   component primitives and a sequence of boolean operations;
 </li>
 <li>the boolean operations union, intersection or difference;</li>
 <li>the standard 3D CSG primitives thus: cone, eccentric cone, cylinder,
 sphere, torus, block, 
 right angular wedge, ellipsoid, tetrahedron and pyramid which are defined in 
 their final position and orientation;
</li>
<li>the boolean result as a boolean operator, thus enabling nested operations;
</li>
<li>any solid model, including, in particular, swept solids as a boolean
operand;</li>
<li>Swept solids which are the swept area solids and the swept face solids which are obtained 
by extruding or sweeping a planar face which may contain holes;
</li>
<li>the half space solid which is a semi-infinite solid on
one side of a surface which may be limited by a box domain. 
</li>
 </inscope>


